SIMPLE: stony
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stony
<hw>Ston"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Stonier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Stoniest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>st⟦amac⟧nig</ets>. See
<er>Stone</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to stone,
consisting of, or abounding in, stone or stones; resembling stone; hard;
<as>as, a <ex>stony</ex> tower; a <ex>stony</ex> cave; <ex>stony</ex>
ground; a <ex>stony</ex> crust</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Converting into stone; petrifying;
petrific.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>stony</qex> dart of senseless cold.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Inflexible; cruel; unrelenting; pitiless; obdurate;
perverse; cold; morally hard; appearing as if petrified; <as>as, a
<ex>stony</ex> heart; a <ex>stony</ex> gaze</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stony coral</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<cref>Stone coral</cref>, under <er>Stone</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stood</ent>⟦br⟧
